text: On 11 April, Women For Change stood at the Union Buildings, carrying more than a symbolic object, we carried the collective grief of a nation. We brought a casket. One that was built 33.8% larger, draped in mourning, and adorned with 5,578 purple beads, - each bead a name, a story, a woman murdered in South Africa in just one year. Inside that casket - the beautiful smiles of some of our sisters we have lost, and the pain of over 150,000 voices who signed our petition, pleading for GBVF to be declared a National Disaster. This campaign wasn’t created for awards - it was born out of heartbreak, out of rage, out of love. To now see it recognised by Ads of the World is deeply moving, not for the spotlight, but because it forces the world to see what our leaders still deny: femicide is South Africa’s real pandemic. Thank you to the amazing team at Edelman Africa and to everyone who poured their heart, creativity, and compassion into this campaign. Our casket will never be buried. It will now travel across cities, towns, and provinces - a solemn protest, a powerful reminder that Women For Change will not stop. We will not be silenced. Not until no woman walks in fear. Not until our cries lead to action. Not until change comes. #womenforchange #UnburyTheTruth #GBVFNationalDisaster #tiktoksouthafrica #womenforchangesa #AmINext #EnoughSaid
hashtags: womenforchange, unburythetruth, gbvfnationaldisaster, tiktoksouthafrica, womenforchangesa, aminext, enoughsaid

text: Dollar Tree Nashville Hot Loaded Fries Bowl 4 Banquet Chicken Nuggets & Fries microwave meals  1 box Dollar Tree Premium Shells and Cheese  1 block Pepper Jack cheese (shredded)  Dill pickle chips (for topping)  Nashville Hot seasoning Oil for frying (vegetable, canola, etc.)   Instructions:  Prep the Ingredients:   Cook the shells and cheese according to the package directions. Set aside and keep warm. Shred the pepper jack cheese.   Fry the Fries and Nuggets:   Heat oil in a deep fryer or heavy pot to 350°F (175°C).  Remove the fries from the microwave meals and deep fry them for about 4 minutes, or until golden and crispy.  Lightly season the fried fries with Nashville Hot seasoning and transfer them to a baking sheet.  Next, fry the chicken nuggets in two batches for about 4 minutes total, flipping halfway through.  Place the cooked fries and nuggets in a warm oven (about 200°F) to stay hot while you prepare the sauce and bowls.   Make the Nashville Hot Sauce:  In a small bowl, mix 2 tablespoons of Nashville Hot seasoning with 4 tablespoons of the hot frying oil. Stir well to form a spicy sauce.   Coat the Chicken:  Toss the fried chicken nuggets in the Nashville Hot sauce until evenly coated. Assemble the Bowls:   Start with a bed of macaroni and cheese.  Evenly distribute the fries and Nashville hot chicken nuggets over the mac and cheese.  Sprinkle shredded pepper jack cheese generously on top.  Finish each bowl with about three dill pickle chips.   Notes:  Serve immediately for the best texture!  You can adjust the Nashville Hot seasoning level depending on your spice preference.  If you don’t have a deep fryer, you can also bake or air fry the fries and nuggets, but deep frying gives it the closest texture to the KFC version. #dollartreedinners #budgetmeals #cheapdinnerideas #nashvillehotchicken #loadedfries #dollartreefoodfinds #comfortfoodonabudget #macandcheesebowls #dollartreerecipes #dinnertransformation

text: Ceremony of Launching Newly-Built Destroyer Takes Place, but Serious Accident Occurs During Process   On May 21, 2025, a ceremony for the launch of a newly-built 5,000-tonnage destroyer was held at Chongjin Shipyard. Kim Jong Un, General Secretary of the Workers' Party of Korea and President of the State Affairs of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea, attended the event. However, a serious accident unfolded during the launch.   Due to inexperienced command and operational carelessness, the stern launch slide detached first and became stranded as the bogie failed to move in parallel. Holes in sections of the warship’s bottom disrupted its balance, while the bow remained stuck on the slipway, leading to the grave incident.   After observing the entire process, the respected Comrade Kim Jong Un delivered a stern assessment, calling it a "serious accident and criminal act" driven by "sheer carelessness, irresponsibility, and unscientific empiricism" that "should never have occurred and cannot be tolerated." He warned that errors by responsible officials from the WPK Central Committee’s Munitions Industry Department, the State Academy of Sciences’ Mechanical Institute, Kim Chaek University of Technology, the Central Ship Design Institute, and Chongjin Shipyard—acts that "lowered the state’s dignity and self-respect"—would be addressed at next month’s Party Central Committee plenary meeting, censuring them for their faults.   Emphasizing that restoring the destroyer is a "political issue" directly tied to state prestige, he ordered unconditional completion before the June plenary meeting, to ensure the patriotic labor of Chongjin and Rajin Shipyard workers yields proud feats boosting defense capabilities. President Donald Trump said the US will engage with Iran in a high-level meeting on Saturday, April 12th. "We have a very big meeting on Saturday, and we're dealing with them directly," Trump told reporters from the Oval Office while sitting next to Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu. The announced meeting is the first known time the US will directly engage with Iran since the previous Trump administration, when it withdrew from the Joint Comprehensive Plan of Action (JCPOA) in 2018. The president refused to detail where the talks would take place or how they would differ from the JCPOA, saying only that they will be "different" and "stronger." Following the US withdrawal from the agreement, the nuclear deal essentially collapsed despite and Iran began rapidly developing its nuclear program. "I think if the talks aren't successful with Iran… Iran is going to be in great danger," Trump said

text: Health Secretary Robert F. Kennedy, Jr. said on Tuesday that the CDC will no longer recommend COVID vaccines for healthy children and pregnant women. Kennedy made the announcement in a video message on social media, standing alongside the FDA commissioner and the head of the National Institutes of Health.  No one from the CDC was featured in the announcement.  The new policy jumps ahead of a planned meeting next month by a CDC panel to address shots for the fall. It also follows the decision by the FDA last week to require new data before approving booster shots for healthy adults and kids. Tuesday's announcement could affect how doctors advise their patients on the vaccines and how insurers cover them. #pbsnewshour #newshour #pbsnews #cdc #covidvaccine #hhs #vaccines #news

Trump’s First Term (2017–2021): Systematic Rollback of Rights Trump’s administration launched an aggressive campaign against the autonomy, equality, and safety of women—often under the guise of “religious freedom,” deregulation, or so-called “traditional values.” 	•	Reproductive Autonomy: 	•	Appointed three Supreme Court justices who helped overturn Roe v. Wade, ending federal protection for abortion rights in Dobbs v. Jackson (2022)—a direct outcome of his judicial legacy. 	•	Expanded the Global Gag Rule, cutting off international aid to organizations that even discussed abortion. 	•	Allowed employers to deny birth control coverage under the ACA based on moral or religious objections. 	•	Workplace and Civil Rights: 	•	Revoked Obama-era protections against pay discrimination and wage transparency. 	•	Scaled back Title IX guidance, weakening protections for survivors of campus sexual assault. 	•	Proposed changes to the EEOC that limited how women could report workplace discrimination. 	•	Cultural Signals: 	•	Repeatedly mocked and dismissed credible women who accused powerful men of abuse. 	•	Refused to take responsibility for over two dozen sexual misconduct allegations against himself, instead smearing his accusers. 	•	Appointed cabinet members and judges with regressive views on gender roles. ⸻ 2. The “Second Term in Waiting” (2024–2025): A New Era of Control and Retaliation Though technically not yet reelected as of today, Trump’s allies have already drafted plans to dramatically expand executive power, including: 	•	Project 2025: A real plan from the Heritage Foundation supported by Trump-aligned figures that aims to dismantle the federal bureaucracy and install loyalists across agencies. 	•	This plan includes removing protections for women, defunding gender equity programs, eliminating the Department of Education’s Office for Civil Rights, and replacing it with “family values” oversight. 	•	It’s hostile to LGBTQ+ women, single mothers, working mothers, and anyone who does not fit into a 1950s patriarchal mold. 	•	State-Level Bans & Surveillance: 	•	Trigger laws enacted during Trump’s first term are now criminalizing abortion in over a dozen states. 	•	Several states have begun monitoring miscarriage data, prosecuting women for seeking care out of state, or even criminalizing travel for abortion—a dangerous precedent that echoes authoritarian control over women’s movement. 	•	Escalating Authoritarian Rhetoric: 	•	Trump and surrogates openly talk about “retribution,” hinting that dissent—especially from vocal women—may be met with punishment or surveillance. 	•	Right-wing influencers routinely threaten journalists, feminists, and educators who advocate for women’s equality, often with Trump’s implicit approval. ⸻ 3. Where We’re Headed If This Isn’t Stopped Unless we reverse course, women in America are looking at a future where: 	•	Federal protection for reproductive healthcare is permanently dismantled. 	•	Gender equality laws are gutted in education, hiring, housing, and healthcare. 	•	Surveillance of women’s bodies becomes normalized—especially for those who are poor, young, immigrant, or single. 	•	Freedom of expression, dress, and movement is policed under moralistic laws designed to “restore traditional order.” 	•	Backlash becomes law: Social progress, especially for women of color and LGBTQ+ women, will not just be halted—it will be criminalized. ⸻ 4. text: A seal in the forest?? Grey seal / Gråsäl I went up before sunrise to see if I could find some beavers at a location where I’ve seen plenty of beaver signs. When I was walking I saw a big grey stone in front of me that I just ignored. Suddenly it moved and I realized that it was a seal in the middle of the forest.  I couldn’t even believe my own eyes and I stayed completely still for a few minutes while we looked at each other. When it looked like he didn’t mind me I calmly sat down and took out my camera from the backpack.  I laid on my stomach and got plenty of pictures when the seal started to crawl towards me, eventually getting too close for me to use my big camera. He even came up to my tripod and gave it a good sniff.  He stayed right next to me, probably like 20 centimeters away, for a little while before he kept crawling in the other direction. I remained in my position until the seal eventually entered the river and swam away.  This is not the end of this encounter but it’s too long for me to include it all in one video. It has a happy ending though, I can tell you that much.  . . . . #seal #sealpup #seals #wildlifephotography #wildlife #nikoneurope  #säl #discovery #bbcearth #natgeoanimals  #sweden #norrtälje

text: If I URGENTLY needed to get a remote job in the next 2 to 3 weeks as a BROKE Nigerian… Here’s the exact strategy I’d follow  1. I’d forget big tech. Focus on global startups and solo founders. Big companies have long pipelines and ATS filters. But small teams are looking for hustlers, not just degrees. I’d target founders on LinkedIn and Twitter who are actively building. These people need help yesterday. 2. I’d package myself   I’d position myself as someone who can wear 3 hats: support, content, and admin. Why? Because small teams don’t hire specialists, they hire people who can figure things out and move fast. 3. I’d create a  portfolio. No time for CV polishing. I’d open Canva or Notion and design a simple page showing: ~ Skills I can offer ~ Tools I’ve used (even free versions count) ~ A Loom video introducing myself (authenticity sells) ~ One or two small sample projects—even if I did them myself. 4. I’d search Twitter and Slack channels everyday. I’d type “remote job,” “hiring,” “freelance help” in search bars every morning and evening. I’d join Slack groups for remote workers, freelancers, and async startups (most of them post direct jobs not listed anywhere else). 5. I’d cold pitch 10 people per day with this message: “Hey [Name], I saw you’re building [Product]. I’m a generalist from Nigeria who can help with [X]. I took a look at your [site/Twitter], and I’d love to support you part-time while you scale. I’ve attached a quick Loom showing what I can offer. I can start today, even if it’s just a trial.” 6. I’d offer value BEFORE asking for pay. Even if it’s 2 days of free work. Why? Because when you’re broke, trust is your currency. You need a way in. If they like your work, payment will follow, plus a testimonial you can flip into the next gig. 7. I’d stop overthinking titles. Whether it’s customer support, virtual assistant, community manager, content researcher, all na remote work. Start with where you are. Your goal is to break in, not to look perfect. 8. Once I land one gig, I’d document everything. I’d turn the process into proof: “Here’s how I landed a remote job in 2 weeks from Nigeria with zero connections.” That post alone can attract recruiters or clients from all over. It’s not  luck.  It’s about packaging, persistence, and proximity to people who are hiring. If you’re broke and serious about remote work, stop scrolling. Start hunting like your next meal depends on it. I’m Akinlabi Idris I share real job search strategies, personal branding tips, and how to make bold career moves from Nigeria to the world.

MSNBC anchor #StephanieRuhle dissected the chaos President #DonaldTrump continues to inject into global markets through erratic tariff policies. “Let’s level set,” she began, noting that “if you talk to businesses big or small, they cannot predict what Trump will do next.” According to Ruhle, Trump’s tariff announcements have become a predictable pattern: “When he makes a tariff announcement, markets tank. When he scales back tariffs, markets soar.” She referenced the Financial Times’ nickname for this dynamic—“the Taco Trade,” short for “Trump always chickens out.” This cycle of whiplash not only destabilizes the markets, Ruhle explained, but also directly impacts consumer sentiment. “When people feel like the tariffs are coming, they worry. When they think that Trump’s not going to go for it, they’re happy.” But the stakes go beyond consumer anxiety. For investors and institutional traders, Ruhle emphasized, the volatility Trump creates is actually an opportunity: “Volatility means volume.” Yet for actual businesses trying to plan and operate, the uncertainty is “paralyzing at best and crippling at worst.” Perhaps most disturbing, Ruhle reported that sources close to Trump’s team have claimed the president “doesn’t actually mind the market reaction when it’s bad.” On the contrary, “he enjoys the power and influence he has over global markets,” able to “erase or create tens of billions” with a single post. This raises major ethical concerns: “If and who is given advance warning on any of these massive market-moving events?” Ruhle left viewers with a chilling reminder—“The answer for now, we do not know. But we and the rest of the world are going to keep watching.” #StephanieRuhle #DonaldTrump #Tariffs #TacoTrade #MarketVolatility #ConsumerSentiment #FinancialTimes #TradePolicy #GlobalMarkets #Investors #BusinessUncertainty #MarketManipulation #MSNBC — Markets move based on what Trump says around tariffs. @stephruhle explains what many are now calling the ‘TACO trade.’ An acronym for ‘Trump Always Chickens Out.’ repost @11thhourmsnbc Help this information get to more voters. text: was pulled from Steam for glorifying r@pe, inc3st, and the domination of women. The outrage was swift—and justified. It’s a vile concept. No question. But these same themes—manipulation, coercion, emotional and physical domination—are romanticized in popular dark romance books and every day. He stalks her. He kidnaps her. He isolates her. He abuses her in the name of love. But he’s “ ” and “  .” One version gets canceled. The other gets a die hard fan base.   ,  . This whole “rules for thee, but not for me” thing is getting old. Because let’s be honest, No Mercy was made for male audiences.  Dark romance? Written by women, for women. And society tells us: “Women won’t act on it.” “They’re not dangerous.” “It’s just fantasy.” But the fantasies in dark romance aren’t just harmless stories—they’re a gateway to constantly seeking the next most obscene, taboo k1nk. And as the k1nks escalate, so do the lines between what’s “erotic” and what’s ab*sive. When women consume this kind of media, they’re not just fantasizing about power play between adults. They’re being trained to crave deeper, darker extremes to get off on. They begin to normalize behavior that mirrors real-world manipulation and exploitation, until suddenly those behaviors include obscene acts like seeking out kids. Books are not innocent. They create thoughts and cultures that can lead to real-world harm. And once that desire becomes ingrained, manipulation, coercion, and abuse start to look normal. The lines between “fantasy” and “reality” are obliterated. This isn’t about defending No Mercy. It’s about holding both forms of media and ALL PEOPLE to the same standard (regardless of gender). Both are harmful. Both deserve to be cancelled.  ✍️   :   Releases July 21st, 2025 • • • #nomercy #steamgames #darkromance #smut #darkromancebooks #hauntingadeline #booklovers #fantasylover #bookloversoftiktok

text: Never lose hope, healing is POSSIBLE! And if your medical team isn’t on board, it’s time to get a new one.  Last year I had a sh*tty oncologist for a few months that left me heartbroken. In my most vulnerable moment, I asked her to give me hope. Her response: “We’ll see. I don’t know many women living for years on this treatment. And unfortunately, it only gets worse from here.” I’m SO GRATEFUL I have the mindset tools to UN-BELIEVE her words as well as the SELF-LOVE to find a new oncologist. She was wrong! I started a new treatment (Enhertu) and my life is so much better in every way - my body is healing, I’m traveling, speaking, skiing, and doing all the things I LOVE!  ✨Nobody knows the future, so why not imagine a good one?✨ Mindset is my biggest focus and I love sharing these tools with other thrivers! If you’re ready to enhance your cancer healing toolbox, join our next Finding Freedom with Cancer Series starting April 2nd (financial support available too). text: During a White House press briefing on Friday, White House Press Secretary Karoline Leavitt addressed concerns over the Safeguard American Voter Eligibility Act, also referred to as the SAVE Act. The act requires documentary proof of U.S. citizenship for those registering to vote, but voting rights groups have argued that the legislation could erect barriers that would make it harder for millions of Americans to vote, including married women who have changed their names. It has been illegal under federal law for non-U.S. citizens to vote in federal elections since 1996 and is already a rare occurrence. Offenders can face fines, prison time for up to a year and deportation. Although noncitizen voting is rare, Republicans and President Trump have argued it to be a pressing threat. The act was approved by the House on Thursday and heads to the Senate next where it will need 60 votes to pass. "Many married women, soon to be married women, are concerned that the new voter ID requirements may inhibit their access to the polls. What assurances can you give women voters in America to ease their concerns?" Jordan Berman, social media content creator, influencer and lawyer asked Leavitt during the White House briefing. "The Democrats have been fear-mongering about this bill, have been saying that married women, if their name has changed, they didn't change it on their identification, would not be able to vote. That is complete fallacy. There are outlined in the bill about how to avoid that," said Leavitt. "I myself as a married woman would not stand before this podium if the president did not support such a common sense measure," she added. #SAVEact #news #Trump #politics

text: via CNN: New Cat Breed “CozyPelt” Resembles a Knitted Sweater, Captivates Feline Enthusiasts March 14, 2025 – A newly developed cat breed, the CozyPelt, is making waves in the pet world with its remarkable resemblance to a hand-knitted sweater. Developed by a team of geneticists and breeders in Norway, this feline’s dense, curly fur forms intricate patterns that mimic the look of woven yarn, giving it a uniquely textured appearance. The CozyPelt’s soft, looped coat is a result of selective breeding between curly-haired breeds like the Selkirk Rex and long-haired Norwegian Forest Cats. Unlike most curly-coated felines, its fur grows in natural cable-knit-like swirls, making it look as if it were wearing a handcrafted wool sweater year-round. According to lead breeder Dr. Erik Lunde, the CozyPelt isn’t just a novelty; it’s also a hypoallergenic breed with a gentle temperament. “We aimed to create a cat with a warm, comforting presence—something that looks as cozy as it feels,” Lunde said. The breed has already drawn significant interest from cat lovers and designers alike, with some comparing its appearance to an artisanal textile masterpiece. While the CozyPelt is still in the early stages of recognition by major cat associations, breeders anticipate it could be formally accepted as an official breed within the next few years. For now, the CozyPelt remains a rare and highly sought-after feline, with waiting lists for kittens already stretching into 2026.

text: This is your sign to make these sweet rolls for your next breakfast/brunch treat…orrr just the next time you need a sweet treat  I love enjoying bright citrusy flavors during the winter to bring a little brightness to my day ☀️ I used @Ambitious Kitchen’s recipe for the rolls themselves which includes the pillowy-soft dough and perfectly sweet lemon-blueberry filling  You can top them with her cream cheese frosting, or opt for this vanilla-bean glaze that’s ooey and gooey and soaks down into the rolls while letting the lemony-blueberry filling really shine—but honestly, you can’t go wrong either way  DOUGH: Zest from 1 large lemon 1/2 cup (100g) granulated sugar 3/4 cup (180g) warm milk (2% or whole milk preferred) 2 1/4 tsp quick rise or active yeast (from 1 (1/4-ounce) package yeast) 1 large egg, at room temperature 1 egg yolk, at room temperature 1/4 cup (57g) salted butter, melted 3 1/4 cups (390g) bread flour, plus more for dusting 3/4 tsp kosher salt FILLING: 1 1/4 cup (194g) fresh or frozen blueberries 1/4 cup (50g) granulated sugar 1 tbsp cornstarch Zest from 1 lemon 1 tsp fresh lemon juice 1/4 tsp almond extract (optional, but recommended) VANILLA-BEAN GLAZE: 1/4 cup melted butter 2 cups powdered sugar 1 tsp vanilla bean paste 1-2 tbsp milk to thin (more or less to desired consistency) Pinch of salt FULL DIRECTIONS FOR DOUGH AND FILLING FOUND ON HER WEBSITE  https://www.ambitiouskitchen.com/lemon-blueberry-sweet-rolls/ If using my vanilla-bean glaze, combine all ingredients in a medium sized bowl and whisk until smooth and pourable. Pour over rolls while still warm  Save this for later and definitely don’t forget about them  Follow me for more yummy ideas ❤️ ️ #sweetrolls #cinnamonrolls #brunch #dessert #lemonblueberry #recipe #cooknourishsavor
hashtags: sweetrolls, cinnamonrolls, brunch, dessert, lemonblueberry, recipe, cooknourishsavor

text: Happy Cinco De Mayo! Let's make a quick and easy salsa! ⬇️ Ingredients:  14 oz can of peeled tomatoes 14 oz can of Rotel 1/4 of an onion 1  Jalapeño Fresh cilantro to taste Lime juice 1 tsp Sugar Salt to taste Directions:  1. Begin by chopping your onion and  jalapeño.  2. Next, add your cilantro 3. Squeeze in the juice of a lime for a zesty kick and add a pinch of salt to enhance the flavors. 4. Blend everything together and let it sit in the fridge for about 30 minutes to let the flavors meld together. 5. And there you have it, a delicious and authentic homemade salsa perfect for Cinco de Mayo! Serve with some crispy tortilla chips or use it as a topping for your favorite Mexican dishes. text: Cheeseburger Garlic Toast is an easy dinner recipe the whole family will love! INGREDIENTS  Garlic Toast (8 count box)  1 lb ground beef  1 onion, chopped  1/2 tsp each of salt and pepper  1 tsp each onion powder and paprika  1 tbsp minced garlic  Shredded American cheese  Burger Sauce (1/2 cup mayo, 1/4 cup ketchup, 1/8 cup mustard, 1 TBSP sweet relish) 2 chopped green onions  INSTRUCTIONS  Cook the Garlic Toast according to the directions on the box. I like to broil it for a few minutes at the end to get it nice and crispy!  Make homemade burger sauce by stirring together mayo, ketchup, mustard, and sweet relish. Set aside.  Brown ground beef and onion in a skillet over medium-high heat and add all of the seasonings. Once the beef is browned, drain any grease and add minced garlic. Stir well.  Use a spoon to push down on each piece of garlic toast. Add the ground beef mixture on top of garlic bread.  Next, add shredded cheese on top and put them back in the oven to melt the cheese. Top with the homemade burger sauce and some chopped green onions. Enjoy! #garlictoast #easyrecipes #dinner #groundbeef #cheeseburger #quickrecipes #easymealideas

text: Rest in Power, Queen  Olorato Mongale, 30, lifeless body was found by community members in Lombardy West, Johannesburg, on 25 May 2025.  She had been last seen just two hours earlier, around 3pm, when she left her home in Athol with a man she had planned to go on a date with. When concerned friends were unable to reach Olorato, they used the “Find My Phone” feature, which led them to a site in Bramley, where her phone and other belongings had been dumped.  Olorato’s family opened a missing persons case at Bramley Police Station around 6pm. However, the police only initiated the search shortly after midnight, citing a lack of available vehicles, as the station had only one functioning vehicle that day. Meanwhile, community members had already found a body in Lombardy West at 5pm and had alerted Sandringham Police Station.  Shockingly, only around 2am, Bramley police were informed that the lifeless body of a woman was found. This was not only a horrific experience for the family - who were still searching for Olorato - but it also raises serious concerns about communication lapses between the Sandringham and Bramley Police Stations, which are in close proximity to each other. Olorato’s family was only able to identify her body the following morning. Despite these setbacks, the investigating detective has been commended by the family for his dedication, consistent communication, and active pursuit of leads in the case. A manhunt is currently underway for a suspect known only as ‘John’, who is believed to be involved in Olorato’s murder. He was last seen driving a white VW Polo bearing a cloned number plate ‘LT 57 JG GP’, which is registered to a Toyota Hilux. We are abaolutely heartbroken over the loss of such a beautiful soul. Another sister was murdered. How many more until we declare GBV and femicide a National Disaster? #WomenForChange #SayHerName #UnburyTheTruth #EnoughSaid #AmINext #womenforchangesa #tiktoksouthafrica #GBVFNationalDisaster #justiceforolorato

text: POV: You’re in a military chopper… and THIS shows up beneath the waves  We were patrolling the coast when the distress call came in. A small fishing boat had gone silent. No radio, no flare. We circled low—and then we saw it. A massive shape beneath the surface… At first, we thought it was a whale. Until the jaw broke the waterline. Rows of prehistoric teeth—easily the size of our rotors—ripped through the waves . The boat was tiny… and directly in its path. We radioed for immediate support, but it was already too close. You could see the moment the crew realized what was coming. This wasn’t just a shark—it was a relic, a nightmare dragged from the deep. We had seconds to decide: intervene, distract, or watch helplessly from above. One wrong move… and we’re next. Comment “DROP A FLARE” if you'd try to distract it from the air  Comment “TOO LATE” if you think the boat was already doomed #oceanmysteries #unbelievablestories #ocean #megalodon #sharkencounter #fyp #Megalodon

#morelike #mostviralvideo #viral #rec #fyp #trending #viral #explore #tiktokviral . . . . . . Bugatti — The renowned designer Ettore Bugatti was an Italian born in Milan. He gained his first experience at the small firm **Prinetti e Stucchi**, then worked for Baron De Dietrich. After developing several passenger cars for him, he moved to the German company **Mathis** in Strasbourg and later to **Deutz** in Cologne. He devoted all his free time to creating a small car, the **Model 10**.   In 1909, Bugatti relocated to Molsheim, then part of Germany (now in eastern France), where he established his own company, Bugatti. Over the next 30 years, the firm produced a series of successful sports and road cars. Virtually all Bugatti vehicles were based on the same chassis, with a ladder frame that also functioned as part of the suspension. The frame's flex was greater than that of the very stiff springs used. At the rear, there were quarter-elliptic springs mounted with their ends facing forward in the direction of travel. For many years, Bugatti stubbornly adhered to this design.

text: Quick & Easy Crockpot Southwest Ranch Chicken Pasta You're going to LOVE this creamy, cheesy comfort food with a kick. Perfect for busy weeknights! Ingredients: • 3 boneless skinless chicken breasts • Salt & pepper to taste • 1 bottle Buffalo IVild Wings Southwest Ranch sauce • 1 bottle heavy whipping cream (use the empty sauce bottle to measure!) • 1 block cream cheese • 1 cup shredded cheddar cheese • 1 cup shredded Parmesan cheese • 1 box pasta of choice (we used penne!) • Optional: Steamed broccoli for added veggies Directions: 1️⃣ Place chicken breasts in the crockpot and season with salt & pepper. 2️⃣ Pour in the bottle of Southwest Ranch sauce. 3️⃣ Fill the empty sauce bottle with heavy whipping cream, shake, and pour over chicken. 4️⃣ Add cream cheese, shredded cheddar, and Parmesan on top. 5️⃣ Cook on high for 4 hours: 6️⃣ Shred the chicken. Meanwhile, cook pasta according to package directions. 7️⃣ Drain pasta and add to the crockpot. Mix everything together and serve! 8️⃣ Top with extra Parmesan and enjoy! ❤️ Save this for your next dinner night and tag me if you try it!  Thinking about adding broccoli next time-what would you add? #easyrecipes #crockpotmeals #ranchchicken #pastarecipe #dinnerideas #easyfamilydinner #slowcookerrecipes #quickdinner #dumpandgo #amyinthekitchen #whatsfordinner #momlifefood #easyhomecooking #viralrecipe #weeknightdinner #comfortfoodrecipes  Shop this post on my LTK ⬇ https://liketk.it/5eCS0

text: BLUE HAIR don’t necessarily have to look 90% of the time TURQUOISE.  You can stop justifying the shade like you would do with your EX: “Damn you know how it is with the green stain….it fades quickly.. green too strong.. I’m sure next time it’ll come out less Aquamarine …” Stop and just open your eyes to the truth honey: BLUES LOOK GREENISH WHEN THE BASE HAS NOT BEEN LIFTED LIGHT ENOUGH FOR THE PRE-TONE TO WORK PROPERLY OR THE PINK INSIDE THE DIRECT DYE. And yes, I said PINK inside the direct dye ,not purple.  Let me explain more the two ways: 1– You can pre-tone and neutralise the yellow with something LILAC ish and the slap the blue dye; it has to be lilac, not purple. If you need purple, then it means the base has not been lifted enough. 2- You can just add PINK directly into the direct dye to neutralise the Green that could come out. I said pink, not red. Garlic Toast Meatball Sandwiches are a quick and easy weeknight dinner!  INGREDIENTS  Texas Toast (8 count box)  1 bag of frozen meatballs 16 oz jar of marinara sauce  Parmesan cheese  8 slices of mozzarella cheese Dried parsley INSTRUCTIONS  Cook Garlic Toast according to the directions on the box.  Next, add the frozen meatballs and marinara sauce to a pan over medium heat and bring that to a simmer. Once simmering cover with a lid and lower the heat. Once the meatballs are hot, sprinkle some Parmesan cheese over the meatballs and stir.   Remove the garlic toast from the oven when golden brown and press down the center with a spoon to form little bread bowls. Place a few meatballs in each piece of garlic toast and top with additional sauce from the pan.  Add mozzarella cheese over the top of each of one and place them back in the oven for a couple more minutes to melt the cheese.   Top with dried parsley and enjoy!

text: The Arthropodans, a formidable hive-mind alien race, hail from the binary star system of Upsilon Andromedae. Ruled by a powerful queen, their society thrives on unity, with every individual connected through a telepathic network centered in her consciousness.  Their impenetrable fortress on the planet Saffar safeguards a mysterious power source, one of the universe’s most closely guarded secrets. Despite countless attacks over millennia, no enemy has breached their defenses, thanks to their advanced warfare tactics and devastating biological weapons. The queen produces three types of eggs: one for reproduction, another for seed bombs with catastrophic explosive power, and a third that releases a gas capable of mind control, assimilating any being into the hive. These tools make the Arthropodans nearly unstoppable. Yet, their hive mind is both their strength and their vulnerability—should the queen fall, their society would collapse into chaos. Biologically immortal and capable of extraordinary feats like leaping 70 feet and wielding immense strength, they avoid direct combat, preferring sabotage and psychological warfare to dominate their foes. Once a neutral, parasitic species, they’ve now allied with the cunning Apexians, lured by promises of galactic territory. This alliance threatens the cosmic balance, as the Apexians, bolstered by the Arthropodans’ might, seek to overthrow the forces of good led by the enigmatic Wise Ones. In this interstellar conflict, the Arthropodans are a wildcard—a force of unity and destruction, their allegiance a harbinger of chaos. The galaxy holds its breath as their next move could decide the fate of all. #sciencefiction #mystery #aiartcommunity #annunaki #movietrailer #movieclips #midjourney #aliens
